Initial setup:
    Let an array of strings called fruits, for example: ["apple", "banana", "cherry", ...]
    Display this list in the UI
Search Input:
    Use the provided input fields
    As the user types into the input, filter the displayed list to include only those items that contain the input
Real-time filteration:
    The list should update as soon as the user types into the search box, without needing to submit
No matches:
    Display a friendly message if no items match the search term.